{"ts":"2026-06-27T11:06:23.858Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"tool","toolName":"read_files","toolCallId":"9w2ewww6","output":[{"query":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/backend/README.md","result":"  1 | # GFF AI Local MVP Backend Foundation\n  2 | \n  3 | Welcome to the local FastAPI MVP backend foundation for the GFF AI Enterprise platform. This module provides local developer API capabilities, SQLite storage connectivity, system health monitoring, and a fully configured local CORS workspace to interface seamlessly with the Next.js frontend.\n  4 | \n  5 | ---\n  6 | \n  7 | ## Architecture Overview\n  8 | \n  9 | The backend uses a standard, modular clean-architecture layout built for Python 3.12+ and FastAPI:\n 10 | \n 11 | ```text\n 12 | backend/\n 13 | ├── app/\n 14 | │   ├── __init__.py\n 15 | │   ├── api.py           # Core endpoints (Health, SystemLogs)\n 16 | │   ├── config.py        # Settings & Pydantic Config Validation\n 17 | │   ├── database.py      # SQLAlchemy DB Connection & Dependency Injection\n 18 | │   ├── main.py          # FastAPI App Entrypoint & CORS Middleware\n 19 | │   ├── models.py        # SQLAlchemy Declarative Models\n 20 | │   └── schemas.py       # Pydantic Schemas (V2)\n 21 | ├── .env.example         # Template for environment configuration\n 22 | ├── .gitignore           # Local development ignores\n 23 | ├── README.md            # Execution manual\n 24 | └── requirements.txt     # Python Dependencies\n 25 | ```\n 26 | \n 27 | ## Features\n 28 | \n 29 | - **Automated DB Bootstrap**: Automatically boots a local SQLite database (`dev.db`) on application launch.\n 30 | - **Enterprise Logs**: A simple, high-performance database logger schema for auditing backend/frontend handshakes.\n 31 | - **Health Verification**: An endpoint at `/api/v1/health` that dynamically validates database status and platform health.\n 32 | - **Next.js Alignment**: Built-in CORS and request timing telemetry middleware matching frontend-dev requirements.\n 33 | - **Clean Interactive Specs**: Automatic redirect of root `/` path to the interactive OpenAPI UI (`/docs`).\n 34 | \n 35 | ---\n 36 | \n 37 | ## Local Setup & Run Guide\n 38 | \n 39 | ### 1. Prerequisites\n 40 | Ensure you have **Python 3.12+** and **pip** installed:\n 41 | ```bash\n 42 | python3 --version\n 43 | pip3 --version\n 44 | ```\n 45 | \n 46 | ### 2. Set Up Virtual Environment\n 47 | Move to the backend folder and create a clean Python virtual environment:\n 48 | ```bash\n 49 | cd backend\n 50 | python3 -m venv venv\n 51 | ```\n 52 | \n 53 | Activate the environment:\n 54 | - **macOS / Linux**:\n 55 |   ```bash\n 56 |   source venv/bin/activate\n 57 |   ```\n 58 | - **Windows**:\n 59 |   ```bash\n 60 |   venv\\Scripts\\activate\n 61 |   ```\n 62 | \n 63 | ### 3. Install Dependencies\n 64 | ```bash\n 65 | pip install -r requirements.txt\n 66 | ```\n 67 | \n 68 | ### 4. Set Up Environment Config\n 69 | Copy the example environment file:\n 70 | ```bash\n 71 | cp .env.example .env\n 72 | ```\n 73 | The defaults in `.env` are pre-tuned for seamless local development with the Next.js local frontend.\n 74 | \n 75 | > ⚠️ **Production Security Warning**:\n 76 | > In local development mode, `JWT_SECRET` defaults to a safe developer-only fallback key. However, for any production deployment, you **MUST** override `JWT_SECRET` in your environment variables with a cryptographically secure, high-entropy key (e.g., generated via `openssl rand -hex 32`). Leaving the default key active in production compromises token verification and authentication security.\n 77 | \n 78 | ### 5. Run the Server\n 79 | Launch the development server via Uvicorn:\n 80 | ```bash\n 81 | uvicorn app.main:app --reload --port 8000\n 82 | ```\n 83 | \n 84 | Once running, you can access:\n 85 | - **Interactive OpenAPI Documentation**: [http://localhost:8000/docs](http://localhost:8000/docs)\n 86 | - **Service Health Check Endpoint**: [http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health](http://localhost:8000/api/v1/health)\n 87 | \n 88 | ---\n 89 | \n 90 | ## API Documentation\n 91 | \n 92 | ### GET `/api/v1/health`\n 93 | Checks backend and database health.\n 94 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n 95 | ```json\n 96 | {\n 97 |   \"status\": \"healthy\",\n 98 |   \"timestamp\": 1719493200.0,\n 99 |   \"database\": {\n100 |     \"status\": \"healthy\",\n101 |     \"error\": null\n102 |   },\n103 |   \"services\": {\n104 |     \"api\": \"healthy\",\n105 |     \"gff_core\": \"operational\"\n106 |   },\n107 |   \"version\": \"1.0.0\"\n108 | }\n109 | ```\n110 | \n111 | ### GET `/api/v1/logs`\n112 | Returns the recent list of system log entries.\n113 | **Response (200 OK)**:\n114 | ```json\n115 | []\n116 | ```\n117 | \n118 | ### POST `/api/v1/logs`\n119 | Creates a test system log.\n120 | **Request Payload**:\n121 | ```json\n122 | {\n123 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n124 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n125 |   \"module\": \"handshake\"\n126 | }\n127 | ```\n128 | **Response (201 Created)**:\n129 | ```json\n130 | {\n131 |   \"id\": 1,\n132 |   \"level\": \"INFO\",\n133 |   \"message\": \"Next.js frontend handshake completed successfully\",\n134 |   \"module\": \"handshake\",\n135 |   \"created_at\": \"2026-06-27T15:10:00.000000\"\n136 | }\n137 | ```","success":true}],"durationMs":2}}
